body: As outlined in my comment in #578.

comment_data.body: @iphydf let me sleep on it, it's already late night
Sure, no hurry. I've invited you to the org. Once you accept, please assign this issue to yourself.

@xhebox also, if you could add back the original function and just have it call the two other functions, we don't break the API. I think we can afford having that function around still, but mark it `@deprecated`. We can remove it later once all client code is off them.

@iphydf 
To be clear, now there's set_video() and set_audio(), and one callback event in namespace bit_rate. And i am going to add bitrate property in namespace audio and video, with set() and get() method, remove the old set().

And what's unclear is:
1. That old callback event is to be replaced by get() completely, or split into two standalone events in namespace audio and video together with get() method; or mark the old one deprecated, then split it into two?

2. To keep the old api, add the old bit_rate_set() function back in another pr? With only old bit_rate_set() there, or need the old callback event either?

1. I don't think we have a get() right now, so we shouldn't add one. Yes, split into two separate events, but still keep the old one around and call that one as well. Mark the old single one as deprecated.

2. Yes, add the old function back. Also keep the old callback event.

@zoff99 @iphydf OK, for not to waste zoff's work, please merge his code first. I coded based on his 732 pr, then i'll open a pr for splitting, and yet another pr to correct name to fix zoff's work and fix the old callbacks.

Or, let me first remove namespace bit_rate completely, then rebase zoff's pr to my pr so that we only need two pr?
this has been done, close it.

title: Make audio/video bit rates "properties" with get() instead of manual functions.
